435 // Load data
436 void US_FeMatch::load( void )
437 {
438  QString file;
439  QStringList files;
440  QStringList parts;
441  lw_triples-> disconnect();
442  lw_triples-> clear();
443  dataList. clear();
444  rawList. clear();
445  excludedScans.clear();
446  triples. clear();
447  speed_steps .clear();
448 
449  dataLoaded = false;
450  buffLoaded = false;
451  haveSim = false;
452  dataLatest = ck_edit->isChecked();
453  int local = dkdb_cntrls->db() ? US_Disk_DB_Controls::DB
454  : US_Disk_DB_Controls::Disk;
455  // US_DataLoader* dialog =
456  // new US_DataLoader( dataLatest, local, rawList, dataList,
457  // triples, workingDir, QString( "velocity" ) );
458 
459  US_DataLoader* dialog =
460  new US_DataLoader( dataLatest, local, rawList, dataList,
461  triples, workingDir, QString( "none" ) );
462 
463  connect( dialog, SIGNAL( changed( bool ) ),
464  this, SLOT( update_disk_db( bool ) ) );
465  connect( dialog, SIGNAL( progress( const QString ) ),
466  this, SLOT( set_progress( const QString ) ) );
467 DbgLv(1) << "LD: exec dialog";
468 
469  if ( dialog->exec() != QDialog::Accepted ) return;
470 
471  edata = &dataList[ 0 ];
472  runID = edata->runID;
473  QString tmst_fpath = US_Settings::resultDir() + "/" + runID + "/"
474  + runID + ".time_state.tmst";
475 
476 
477  qDebug() << "RUNID --- " << runID;
478  // Get speed steps from disk or DB experiment (and maybe timestate)
479 
480  if ( local == US_Disk_DB_Controls::DB )
481  { // Fetch the speed steps for the experiment from the database
482  workingDir = tr( "(database)" );
483 
484  US_Passwd pw;
485  US_DB2* dbP = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
486  QStringList query;
487  QString expID;
488  int idExp = 0;
489  query << "get_experiment_info_by_runID"
490  << runID
491  << QString::number( US_Settings::us_inv_ID() );
492  dbP->query( query );
493 
494  if ( dbP->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK )
495  {
496  dbP->next();
497  idExp = dbP->value( 1 ).toInt();
498  US_SimulationParameters::speedstepsFromDB( dbP, idExp, speed_steps );
499  }
500 DbgLv(1)<<"LD: from database";
501 
502  // Check out whether we need to read TimeState from the DB
503 
504  bool newfile = US_TimeState::dbSyncToLF( dbP, tmst_fpath, idExp );
505 DbgLv(0) << "LD: newfile" << newfile << "idExp" << idExp
506  << "tmst_fpath" << tmst_fpath;
507  }
508 
509  else
510  { // Read run experiment file and parse out speed steps
511  workingDir = workingDir.section( workingDir.left( 1 ), 4, 4 );
512  workingDir = workingDir.left( workingDir.lastIndexOf( "/" ) );
513  QString expfpath = workingDir + "/" + runID + "."
514  + edata->dataType + ".xml";
515  QFile xfi( expfpath );
516 
517  if ( xfi.open( QIODevice::ReadOnly ) )
518  { // Read and parse "<speedstep>" lines in the XML
519  QXmlStreamReader xmli( &xfi );
520 
521  while ( ! xmli.atEnd() )
522  {
523  xmli.readNext();
524 
525  if ( xmli.isStartElement() && xmli.name() == "speedstep" )
526  {
527  SP_SPEEDPROFILE sp;
528  US_SimulationParameters::speedstepFromXml( xmli, sp );
529  speed_steps << sp;
530  }
531  }
532 
533  xfi.close();
534  }
535  }
536 
537  QFileInfo check_file( tmst_fpath );
538  if ( check_file.exists() && check_file.isFile() )
539  { // Get speed_steps from an existing timestate file
540  simparams.simSpeedsFromTimeState( tmst_fpath );
541  simparams.speedstepsFromSSprof();
542 //*DEBUG*
543 int essknt=speed_steps.count();
544 int tssknt=simparams.speed_step.count();
545 DbgLv(1) << "LD: (e)ss knt" << essknt << "(t)ss knt" << tssknt;
546 for ( int jj = 0; jj < qMin( essknt, tssknt ); jj++ )
547 {
548  DbgLv(1) << "LD: jj" << jj << "(e) tf tl wf wl scns"
549  << speed_steps[jj].time_first
550  << speed_steps[jj].time_last
551  << speed_steps[jj].w2t_first
552  << speed_steps[jj].w2t_last
553  << speed_steps[jj].scans;
554  DbgLv(1) << "LD: (t) tf tl wf wl scns"
555  << simparams.speed_step[jj].time_first

557  << simparams.speed_step[jj].w2t_first
558  << simparams.speed_step[jj].w2t_last
559  << simparams.speed_step[jj].scans;
560  }
561 //*DEBUG*
562  int kstep = speed_steps.count();
563  int kscan = speed_steps[ 0 ].scans;
564 
565  //ALEXEY: #speed steps from TimeStamp can be bigger than what's read from DB??
566  for ( int jj = 0; jj < simparams.speed_step.count(); jj++ )
567  {
568  if ( jj < kstep )
569  {
570  kscan = speed_steps[ jj ].scans;
571  speed_steps[ jj ] = simparams.speed_step[ jj ];

575

581  << speed_steps[jj].w2t_first

583  << speed_steps[jj].scans;

586

588  int ntriples = triples.size();
589  DbgLv(1) << "LD: Load: no of speed steps" << nssp;
590 
591  if ( nssp > 0 )
592  {

595  int stm1 = speed_steps[ ii ].time_first;

605

607  { // Data times beyond speed step ranges, so flag use of data ranges
608  nssp = 0;
609  qDebug() << "Data is beyond range ex:" << etm1 << etm2 << "ss:" << stm1 << stm2;
610  //speed_steps.clear();
611  break;
612  }
613  }
614  }
615  }
616 
617  exp_steps = ( nssp > 0 );
618  dat_steps = !exp_steps;
619 DbgLv(1) << "LD: after if block, nssp=" << nssp << " exp_steps" << exp_steps;
620 
621  qApp->processEvents();
622

630

635  double avgTemp = edata->average_temperature();

809 // Data plot
810 void US_FeMatch::data_plot( void )
811 {
812  dataPlotClear( data_plot2 );
813 
814  if ( !dataLoaded )
815  return;
816 
817  bool in_db = dkdb_cntrls->db();
818  int drow = lw_triples->currentRow();
819  edata = &dataList[ drow ];
820  QString triple = QString( triples.at( drow ) ).replace( " / ", "/" );
821  QString dataType = tr( "Absorbance" );
822  if ( edata->dataType == "RI" &&
823  ! has_intensity_profile( edata->runID, in_db ) )
824  dataType = tr( "Intensity" );
825  if ( edata->dataType == "WI" ) dataType = tr( "Intensity" );
826  if ( edata->dataType == "IP" ) dataType = tr( "Interference" );
827  if ( edata->dataType == "FI" ) dataType = tr( "Fluourescence" );
828  data_plot2->setTitle(
829  tr( "Velocity Data for " ) + triple + " of\n" + edata->runID );
830  data_plot2->setAxisTitle( QwtPlot::yLeft,
831  dataType + tr( " at " ) + edata->wavelength + tr( " nm" ) );
832  data_plot2->setAxisTitle( QwtPlot::xBottom,
833  tr( "Radius (cm)" ) );
834 
835  QwtPlotGrid* data_grid = us_grid( data_plot2 );
836  data_grid->setMajorPen(
837  QPen( US_GuiSettings::plotMinGrid(), 0, Qt::DotLine ) );
838 
839  int scan_nbr = 0;
840  int from = (int)ct_from->value();
841  int to = (int)ct_to ->value();
842 
843  int points = edata->pointCount();
844  int count = points;
845 
846  if ( haveSim )
847  {
848  count = sdata->pointCount();
849  count = points > count ? points : count;
850  }
851 
852  QVector< double > vecr( count );
853  QVector< double > vecv( count );
854  double* rr = vecr.data();
855  double* vv = vecv.data();
856 
857  QString title;
858  QwtPlotCurve* cc;
859  QPen pen_red( Qt::red );
860  QPen pen_plot( US_GuiSettings::plotCurve() );
861 
862  // See if a color map gradient has been loaded
863  QList< QColor > mcolors;
864  int nmcols = plotLayout2->map_colors( mcolors );
865  if ( nmcols == 1 )
866  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ 0 ] );
867 
868  // Calculate basic parameters for other functions
869  double avgTemp = edata->average_temperature();
870  solution.density = le_density ->text().toDouble();
871  solution.viscosity = le_viscosity->text().toDouble();
872  solution.manual = manual;
873  solution.vbar20 = le_vbar ->text().toDouble();
874  solution.vbar = US_Math2::calcCommonVbar( solution_rec, avgTemp );
875 
876  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, solution );
877 
878  dscan = &edata->scanData.last();
879  int point = US_DataIO::index( dataList[ drow ].xvalues,
880  dataList[ drow ].baseline );
881  point = ( point < 5 ) ? 5 : point;
882  double baseline = 0.0;
883 
884  for ( int jj = point - 5; jj < point + 6; jj++ )
885  baseline += dscan->rvalues[ jj ];
886 
887  baseline /= 11.0;
888 
889  // Draw curves
890  for ( int ii = 0; ii < scanCount; ii++ )
891  {
892  if ( excludedScans.contains( ii ) ) continue;
893 
894  if ( nmcols > 1 )
895  { // Get pen plot color from gradient
896  int colx = ii % nmcols;
897  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ colx ] );
898  }
899 
900  scan_nbr++;
901  bool highlight = ( scan_nbr >= from && scan_nbr <= to );
902 
903  dscan = &edata->scanData[ ii ];
904 
905  for ( int jj = 0; jj < points; jj++ )
906  {
907  rr[ jj ] = edata->radius( jj );
908  vv[ jj ] = edata->value ( ii, jj );
909  }
910 
911  title = tr( "Curve " ) + QString::number( ii ) + tr( " in range" );
912  cc = us_curve( data_plot2, title );
913 
914  if ( highlight )
915  cc->setPen( pen_red );
916  else
917  cc->setPen( pen_plot );
918 
919  cc->setSamples( rr, vv, points );
920  }
921 
922  // Plot simulation
923  if ( haveSim )
924  {
925  double rl = edata->radius( 0 );
926  double vh = edata->value( scanCount - 1, points - 1 );
927  rl -= 0.05;
928  vh += ( vh - edata->value( 0, 0 ) ) * 0.05;
929  double rnoi = 0.0;
930  double tnoi = 0.0;
931  bool have_ri = ri_noise.count > 0;
932  bool have_ti = ti_noise.count > 0;
933 
934  double rmsd = 0.0;
935  int kpts = 0;
936 
937  for ( int ii = 0; ii < scanCount; ii++ )
938  {
939  if ( excludedScans.contains( ii ) ) continue;
940 
941  points = sdata->pointCount();
942  count = 0;
943  double rp = 0.0;
944  double vp = 0.0;
945  double da = 0.0;
946  rnoi = have_ri ? ri_noise.values[ ii ] : 0.0;
947 
948  for ( int jj = 0; jj < points; jj++ )
949  { // accumulate coordinates of simulation curve
950  tnoi = have_ti ? ti_noise.values[ jj ] : 0.0;
951  rp = sdata->radius( jj );
952  vp = sdata->value( ii, jj ) + rnoi + tnoi;
953  da = edata->value( ii, jj );
954  rmsd += sq( da - vp );
955  kpts++;
956  if ( rp > rl )
957  {
958  rr[ count ] = rp;
959  vv[ count++ ] = vp;
960  }
961  }
962  title = "SimCurve " + QString::number( ii );
963  cc = us_curve( data_plot2, title );
964  cc->setPen ( pen_red );
965  cc->setSamples( rr, vv, count );
966  }
967 
968  rmsd /= (double)kpts;
969  le_variance->setText( QString::number( rmsd ) );
970  rmsd = sqrt( rmsd );
971  le_rmsd ->setText( QString::number( rmsd ) );
972 //*DEBUG
973 double vsum=0.0;
974 for ( int ii=0; ii<scanCount; ii++ )
975 {
976  if ( excludedScans.contains( ii ) ) continue;
977  for( int jj=0; jj<points; jj++ )
978  vsum += sq(sdata->value(ii,jj));
979 }
980 DbgLv(1) << "VSUM=" << vsum;
981 int hh=sdata->pointCount()/2;
982 int ss=sdata->scanCount();
983 DbgLv(1) << "SDAT 0-3"<< sdata->value(0,hh) << sdata->value(1,hh)
984  << sdata->value(2,hh) << sdata->value(3,hh);
985 DbgLv(1) << "SDAT *-n" << sdata->value(ss-4,hh) << sdata->value(ss-3,hh)
986  << sdata->value(ss-2,hh) << sdata->value(ss-1,hh);
987 if(sdata->value(ss-1,hh)==0.0) {
988  for (int js=0;js<scanCount;js++)
989  DbgLv(1) << "SDAT js" << js << "sd" << sdata->value(js,hh) << "ed" << edata->value(js,hh);
990 }
991 //*DEBUG
992 
993 //DbgLv(1) << "STEP0 durmin dlymin w2tf w2tl timf timl"
994  }
995 
996  else
997  { // No simulation exists yet
998  dataPlotClear( data_plot1 );
999  data_plot1->setTitle( tr( "Residuals" ) );
1000  data_plot1->replot();
1001  }
1002 
1003  data_plot2->replot();
1004 
1005  return;
1006 }

1845 // Adjust model components based on buffer, vbar, and temperature
1846 void US_FeMatch::adjust_model()
1847 {
1848  model = model_used;
1849 
1850  // build model component correction factors
1851  double avgTemp = edata->average_temperature();
1852  double vbar20 = le_vbar ->text().toDouble();
1853 
1854  solution.density = le_density ->text().toDouble();
1855  solution.viscosity = le_viscosity->text().toDouble();
1856  solution.manual = manual;
1857  solution.vbar20 = vbar20;
1858  solution.vbar = US_Math2::calcCommonVbar( solution_rec, avgTemp );
1859 // solution.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( solution.vbar20, avgTemp );
1860 
1861  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, solution );
1862 
1863  double scorrec = solution.s20w_correction;
1864  double dcorrec = solution.D20w_correction;
1865  double mc_vbar = model.components[ 0 ].vbar20;
1866  // Set constant-vbar and constant-ff0 flags
1867  cnstvb = model.constant_vbar();
1868  cnstff = model.constant_ff0();
1869 
1870  US_Math2::SolutionData sd;
1871  sd.density = solution.density;
1872  sd.viscosity = solution.viscosity;
1873  sd.vbar20 = solution.vbar20;
1874  sd.vbar = solution.vbar;
1875  sd.manual = solution.manual;
1876 DbgLv(1) << "Fem:Adj: avgT" << avgTemp << "scorr dcorr" << scorrec << dcorrec;
1877 
1878  if ( cnstvb && mc_vbar != sd.vbar20 && mc_vbar != 0.0 )
1879  { // Use vbar from the model component, instead of from the solution
1880  sd.vbar20 = mc_vbar;
1881  sd.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( sd.vbar20, avgTemp );
1882  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, sd );
1883  scorrec = sd.s20w_correction;
1884  dcorrec = sd.D20w_correction;
1885 DbgLv(1) << "Fem:Adj: cnstvb" << cnstvb << " scorr dcorr" << scorrec << dcorrec;
1886  }
1887 DbgLv(1) << "Fem:Adj: avgT" << avgTemp << "vb20 vb" << sd.vbar20 << sd.vbar;
1888 
1889  // Convert to experiment space: adjust s,D based on solution,temperature
1890 
1891  for ( int jj = 0; jj < model.components.size(); jj++ )
1892  {
1893  US_Model::SimulationComponent* sc = &model.components[ jj ];
1894 
1895  sc->vbar20 = ( sc->vbar20 == 0.0 ) ? vbar20 : sc->vbar20;
1896 
1897  if ( ! cnstvb )
1898  { // Set s,D corrections based on component vbar
1899  sd.vbar20 = sc->vbar20;
1900  sd.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( sd.vbar20, avgTemp );
1901  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, sd );
1902  scorrec = sd.s20w_correction;
1903  dcorrec = sd.D20w_correction;
1904  }
1905 
1906 double s20w=sc->s;
1907 double d20w=sc->D;
1908  sc->s /= scorrec;
1909  sc->D /= dcorrec;
1910 DbgLv(1) << "Fem:Adj: s20w D20w" << s20w << d20w
1911  << "s D" << sc->s << sc->D << " jj" << jj << "vb20 vb" << sc->vbar20 << sd.vbar;
1912 
1913  if ( sc->extinction > 0.0 )
1914  sc->molar_concentration = sc->signal_concentration / sc->extinction;
1915  }
1916 
1917 }

2508 // Interpolate an sdata y (readings) value for a given x (radius)
2509 double US_FeMatch::interp_sval( double xv, double* sx, double* sy, int ssize )
2510 {
2511  for ( int jj = 1; jj < ssize; jj++ )
2512  {
2513  if ( xv == sx[ jj ] )
2514  {
2515  return sy[ jj ];
2516  }
2517 
2518  if ( xv < sx[ jj ] )
2519  { // given x lower than array x: interpolate between point and previous
2520  int ii = jj - 1;
2521  double dx = sx[ jj ] - sx[ ii ];
2522  double dy = sy[ jj ] - sy[ ii ];
2523  return ( sy[ ii ] + ( xv - sx[ ii ] ) * dy / dx );
2524  }
2525  }
2526 
2527  // given x position not found: interpolate using last two points
2528  int jj = ssize - 1;
2529  int ii = jj - 1;
2530  double dx = sx[ jj ] - sx[ ii ];
2531  double dy = sy[ jj ] - sy[ ii ];
2532  return ( sy[ ii ] + ( xv - sx[ ii ] ) * dy / dx );
2533 }

2572 // Calculate average baseline absorbance
2573 double US_FeMatch::calc_baseline( int drow ) const
2574 {

2675 // Calculate residual absorbance values (data - sim - noise)
2676 void US_FeMatch::calc_residuals()
2677 {
2678  int dsize = edata->pointCount();
2679  int ssize = sdata->pointCount();
2680  QVector< double > vecxx( dsize );
2681  QVector< double > vecsx( ssize );
2682  QVector< double > vecsy( ssize );
2683  double* xx = vecxx.data();
2684  double* sx = vecsx.data();
2685  double* sy = vecsy.data();
2686  double yval;
2687  double sval;
2688  double rmsd = 0.0;
2689  double tnoi = 0.0;
2690  double rnoi = 0.0;
2691  bool ftin = ti_noise.count > 0;
2692  bool frin = ri_noise.count > 0;
2693  bool matchd = ( dsize == ssize );
2694  int kpts = 0;
2695 DbgLv(1) << "CALC_RESID: matchd" << matchd << "dsize ssize" << dsize << ssize;
2696 int kexcls=0;
2697 
2698  QVector< double > resscan;
2699 
2700  resids .clear();
2701  resscan.resize( dsize );
2702 
2703  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dsize; jj++ )
2704  {
2705  xx[ jj ] = edata->radius( jj );
2706  }
2707 
2708  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ssize; jj++ )
2709  {
2710  sx[ jj ] = sdata->radius( jj );
2711  if ( sx[ jj ] != xx[ jj ] ) matchd = false;
2712  }
2713 
2714  for ( int ii = 0; ii < scanCount; ii++ )
2715  {
2716  bool usescan = !excludedScans.contains( ii );
2717 if(!usescan) kexcls++;
2718 
2719  rnoi = frin ? ri_noise.values[ ii ] : 0.0;
2720 
2721  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ssize; jj++ )
2722  {
2723  sy[ jj ] = sdata->value( ii, jj );
2724  }
2725 
2726  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dsize; jj++ )
2727  { // Calculate the residuals and the RMSD
2728  tnoi = ftin ? ti_noise.values[ jj ] : 0.0;
2729 
2730  if ( matchd )
2731  sval = sy[ jj ];
2732  else
2733  sval = interp_sval( xx[ jj ], sx, sy, ssize );
2734 
2735  yval = edata->value( ii, jj ) - sval - rnoi - tnoi;
2736 
2737  if ( usescan )
2738  {
2739  rmsd += sq( yval );
2740  kpts++;
2741  }
2742 
2743  resscan[ jj ] = yval;
2744  }
2745 
2746  resids << resscan;
2747  }
2748 
2749  rmsd /= (double)( kpts );
2750  le_variance->setText( QString::number( rmsd ) );
2751  rmsd = sqrt( rmsd );
2752  le_rmsd ->setText( QString::number( rmsd ) );
2753 DbgLv(1) << "CALC_RESID: matchd" << matchd << "kexcls" << kexcls << "rmsd" << rmsd;
2754 }

2841 // Compose data details text
2842 QString US_FeMatch::run_details( void )

3868 // Write a file containing a model distributions table in CSV format
3869 void US_FeMatch::model_table( QString mdtFile )
3870 {
3871  // Get the total concentration
3872  int ncomp = model_used.components.size();
3873  if ( ncomp == 0 )
3874  return;
3875  QFile mdt_f( mdtFile );
3876  if ( ! mdt_f.open( QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text ) )
3877  return;
3878  double sum_c = 0.0;
3879 
3880  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ncomp; ii++ )
3881  {
3882  double conc = model_used.components[ ii ].signal_concentration;
3883  sum_c += conc;
3884  }
3885 
3886  // Write out the comma-separated-values text fields
3887  QTextStream ts( &mdt_f );
3888  const QString dquote( "\"" );
3889  const QString comma( "," );
3890  const QString endln( "\n" );
3891 
3892  // Write the header line
3893  ts << dquote + "Molec.Weight" + dquote + comma
3894  + dquote + "S_Apparent" + dquote + comma
3895  + dquote + "S_20_W" + dquote + comma
3896  + dquote + "D_Apparent" + dquote + comma
3897  + dquote + "D_20_W" + dquote + comma
3898  + dquote + "f/f0" + dquote + comma
3899  + dquote + "Vbar20" + dquote + comma
3900  + dquote + "Concentration" + dquote + comma
3901  + dquote + "Conc.Percent" + dquote + endln;
3902 
3903  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ncomp; ii++ )
3904  { // Write each component line
3905  double conc = model_used.components[ ii ].signal_concentration;
3906  double perc = 100.0 * conc / sum_c;
3907  ts << dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e",
3908  model_used.components[ ii ].mw ) + dquote + comma +
3909  dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e",
3910  model .components[ ii ].s ) + dquote + comma +
3911  dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e",
3912  model_used.components[ ii ].s ) + dquote + comma +
3913  dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e",
3914  model .components[ ii ].D ) + dquote + comma +
3915  dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e",
3916  model_used.components[ ii ].D ) + dquote + comma +
3917  dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e",
3918  model_used.components[ ii ].f_f0 ) + dquote + comma +
3919  dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e",
3920  model_used.components[ ii ].vbar20 ) + dquote + comma +
3921  dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e",
3922  conc ) + dquote + comma +
3923  dquote + QString().sprintf( "%5.2f %%",
3924  perc ) + dquote + endln;
3925  }
3926 
3927  int nreac = model_used.associations.size();
3928  if ( nreac == 0 )
3929  return;
3930 
3931  // Write the header line
3932  ts << dquote + "Reaction" + dquote + comma
3933  + dquote + "K_dissociation" + dquote + comma
3934  + dquote + "k_off_Rate" + dquote + endln;
3935 
3936  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nreac; ii++ )
3937  { // Write each reaction line
3938  double k_d = model_used.associations[ ii ].k_d;
3939  double k_off = model_used.associations[ ii ].k_off;
3940  ts << dquote + QString().sprintf( "%4d", ii ) + dquote + comma
3941  + dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e", k_d ) + dquote + comma
3942  + dquote + QString().sprintf( "%10.4e", k_off ) + dquote + endln;
3943  }
3944 }

4027 {
4028  QString ripxml;
4029 
4030  if ( in_db )

4039  return false; // No DB records means no profile
4040  db.next();
4041  ripxml = db.value( 16 ).toString(); // Otherwise get profile text
4042  }
4043 
4044  else

4046  QString filename = US_Settings::resultDir() + "/" + runID + "/"
4047  + runID + ".RIProfile.xml";
4048 
4049  QFile fi( filename );
4050

4052  return false; // No file means no intensity profile
4053 
4054  ripxml = fi.readAll(); // Otherwise read profile text
4055  fi.close();
4056  }
4057
